ednesday claiming that \\\"no one had won\\\" and asked \\\"republican forces\\\" to form a \\\"solid majority\\\" to govern.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.257055702795135e-55, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9999983581596843, \"rank\": 1.5727854357879827e-06, \"text\": \"republican\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his silence\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"grouping\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"the radical and centre-left and greens\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"his own centrist camp\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"second place\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 827}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday's election\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 848}, {\"ngram\": \"an open letter\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"solid majority\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French president called the snap election in the wake of large gains made by Marine Le Pen's far-right National Rally (RN) party in European elections in June.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 999, \"end\": 1015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}, {\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_European_Parliament_election\", \"score\": 0.9999999892434063, \"rank\": 1.0755798800032408e-08, \"text\": \"European elections\", \"types\": [\"Q40231\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_European_Parliament_election\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_European_Parliament_election\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the snap election\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1052}, {\"ngram\": \"large gains\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RN then performed strongly in the first round of voting in the French parliamentary elections, before an agreement by the leftist bloc and Macron's Together grouping meant that more than 200 candidates dropped out before the second round in an effort to prevent the vote against RN from being split.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1222, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_French_legislative_election\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.863571986243919e-25, \"text\": \"French parliamentary elections\", \"types\": [\"Q40231\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2