ne_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1864760017868205e-14, \"text\": \"Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The result\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1470}, {\"ngram\": \"NFP\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"around 180 seats\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"the 577-seat parliament\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All three blocs are more than 100 seats short of an absolute majority of 289 seats.\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All three blocs\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"an absolute majority\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"289 seats\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With weeks of talks expected over who could become the next prime minister, and what a government will look like, Mr Macron's ally and current prime minister Gabriel Attal offered his resignation but has been asked to stay on by Mr Macron.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.257055702795135e-55, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}, {\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.257055702795135e-55, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"weeks\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"talks\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"the next prime minister\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"a government\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"current prime minister\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"his resignation\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faced with a hung parliament, Mr Macron called in his open letter for a coalition of all MPs, with the exception of the populist National Rally and the radical left France Unbowed (LFI) party, who are a significant part of the NFP alliance but are seen as almost as extreme as RN by many in the French president's centrist group.\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1947, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.257055702795135e-55, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2043, \"end\": 2057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 2141, \"end\": 2144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.515470097923526e-12, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 2191, \"end\": 2193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0966464018987188e-30, \"text\": \"RN\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a hung parliament\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"his open letter\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1979}, {\"ngram\": \"a coalition\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 1995}, {\"ngram\": \"all MPs\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"the exception\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2026}, {\"ngram\": \"the radical left France Unbowed (LFI) party\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"a significant part\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hitting back, Sophie Binet, leader of the CGT union, said on Thursday that Mr Macron was in denial about the result of the election and should appoint as prime minister whoever the NFP picks.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2259, \"end\": 2265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"score\": 0.9999127283330135, \"rank\": 8.693330199260478e-05, \"text\": \"Sophie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\"}, {\"begin\": 2266, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.323829702443094e-13, \"text\": \"Binet\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\"}, {\"begin\": 2287, \"end\": 2290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.652858194717461e-25, \"text\": \"CGT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\"}, {\"begin\": 2323, \"end\": 2329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.257055702795135e-55, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"leader\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"denial\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2343}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2360}, {\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2376}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2413}, {\"ngram\": \"whoever\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Members of the alliance have been trying all week to agree on a name and a strategy to govern without a majority.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Members\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"the alliance\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2505}, {\"ngram\": \"a strategy\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Emmanuel Macronmust snap out of his denialism.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Emmanuel Macronmust\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2572}, {\"ngram\": \"his denialism\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has lost the election...\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's like Louis XVI holed up at Versailles.\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XVI\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.359374128975232e-15, \"text\": \"Louis XVI\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XVI\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XVI\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Versailles\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2670}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He must listen to the country and stop being so disconnected,\\\" Ms Binet said on LCI television.\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2752, \"end\": 2755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Landing_Craft_Infantry\", \"score\": 0.5632383165839796, \"rank\": 0.7138070540104268, \"text\": \"LCI\", \"types\": [\"Q11446\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Landing_Craft_Infantry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Landing_Craft_Infantry\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2701}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms Binet\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Binet hinted that protests could continue during the Olympics if Macron did not comply, saying \\\"at this stage, we have not planned any strikes during the Olympics, but if Macron continues to throw petrol on to the flames...\\\" The Olympic Games start on 26 July.\", \"from\": 2769, \"to\": 3032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2772, \"end\": 2777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.323829702443094e-13, \"text\": \"Binet\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\